      "text": {
        "Aesthetics & Engagement With Nature &#8594; Vision": "Greenspace may help protect against the development of myopia (near-sightedness).",
        "Evidence": [
          "[1]  As greenness in the daily environment (home, school, and commute) increased by an interquartile range, the risk of using glasses among children age 7-10 decreased by 22% (95% CI: 6%, 35%) (<a href=\"https://awseastaging.epa.gov/EcoHealthBrowser/bibliography.html#Dadvand_SunyA_2017\" target=\"_blank\">Dadvand et al., 2017</a>; n=2727, Barcelona, Spain)."
        ]
      }
