          "[3]  Atrazine is an herbicide with peak contamination in drinking water from May to September. There was a 37% increased risk of small for gestational age in births where the third trimester overlapped wholly or in part with this period. If the entire third trimester took place within the peak period, there was a 54% increased risk of small for gestational age (<a href=\"https://awseastaging.epa.gov/EcoHealthBrowser/bibliography.html#Villanueva_2005\" target=\"_blank\">Villanueva et al., 2005</a>; n=3,510 births, France)."
